cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CE 

This paper involves the development of a data infrastructure and computational tools for drug repurposing using chemical ontologies. The use of ontologies and machine learning techniques suggests that this paper could fall under the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Databases (cs.DB), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The two drug-repurposing systems described in the paper, one based on information retrieval and the other based on non-negative matrix factorization, suggest that this paper could also fall under the categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
